The Helper’s House Church has announced the return of its football tournament 12 years after the first edition in 2010. Organisers of the tournament disclosed this on Monday during the opening day ceremony and the draws at its Lagos church. The church explained that during the long hiatus from the maiden edition, it has engaged in humanitarian activities including sensitisation exercises, skill acquisition programmes, among others. According to The Helper’s House’s Senior Pastor, Niyi Adekunle, the need to keep the youth meaningfully active and productive necessitated the return of the tournament tagged, ‘The Helper’s House Unity Cup 2022’. An associate pastor of the church, Kunle Oludapo, expressed optimism that the tournament will expose the players to the world.   We are ready for the Senegalese, Falconets coach assures     Eunisell sponsorship aided our superb performance – Rivers…     Super Eagles hit Ghana for World Cup play off   Oludapo disclosed that the tournament will continue to run annually. On the draws day, male teams of 16 club sides were grouped into four while female teams of eight club sides were grouped into two. The tournament kicking off March 28 at the Anthony Village Recreation Center will see the male teams slugging it out for the grand prize of N400,000 with the teams in second and third places going home with N300,000 and N200,000 respectively. The winning prize for the best female team is N250,000 while the second place gets N150,000. The finalists for the male and female will leave with jerseys. Four matches including a single female match will take place daily till April 18.